4
5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR ATTORNEYS TO APPEAR REMOTELY IN
6 COURT; ESTABLISHING THAT PUBLIC DEFENDERS MAY APPEAR REMOTELY IN NONSUBSTANTIVE
7 HEARINGS; PROVIDING THAT A COURT MAY ORDER AN ATTORNEY TO APPEAR IN PERSON IF GOOD
8 CAUSE EXISTS; AND PROVIDING DEFINITIONS.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Remote appearance by counsel -- definitions. (1) All courts shall are
13 encouraged to establish a consistent, predictable process for attorneys to appear remotely in court and are
14 encouraged to develop formal practice standards for remote representation.
15 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (2)(b), an attorney assigned pursuant to 47-1-104(4) who
16 is appearing in court for a nonsubstantive hearing may appear remotely. IF APPEARING REMOTELY, THE ATTORNEY
17 SHALL USE A CAMERA TO APPEAR ONSCREEN.
18 (b) A court may order an attorney to appear in person for a specific nonsubstantive hearing if the
19 court finds good cause for the attorney's personal presence and issues an order providing the legal and factual
20 basis for good cause at least 5 business days before the specified hearing.
21 (c) For the purposes of this subsection (2), the term "good cause" includes a court's lack of
22 available technological resources or capacity to accommodate having the attorney appear remotely.
23 (3) As used in this section, the following definitions apply:
24 (a) "Appear remotely" means to participate in a hearing through the use of two-way electronic
25 audio-video communication that allows:
26 (i) all of the participants to be heard in the courtroom by all present and allows the party speaking
27 to be seen; and
28 (ii) a defendant or person represented by counsel assigned pursuant to 47-1-104(4) to see and
